column4: Primary Care Organisations (Eng) Apr 2011 Names and Codes

This file contains names and codes for Primary Care Organisation in England as at April 2011. Primary Care Organisations (PCOs) were reorganised on 1st October 2006 as part of the restructuring of the NHS in England. There are 151 Primary Care Organisations (PCOs) in England, made up of 146 Primary Care Trusts (PCTs), 4 Care Trusts (CTs) and 1 Care Trust Plus. CTs are similar to PCTs, but with responsibilities for social as well as health care. This file contains the new 9 character coding as well as the old 3 character coding. For more information, please use the following link to the Code History Database (CHD) - http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/guide-method/geography/products/names--codes-and-look-ups/code-history-database/index.html.

This data was migrated from ONS Geography legacy systems The old style codes have been supplied by Organisational Data Services (ODS). The names have been supplied by Department of Health (DH). The new 9 character codes were created by ONS.
